docstring.short_description: The Calculate Circle Move node moves in a circle relative to a reference plane. This node's output can be fed into a move keyframes node to create a movement along a circular path of a given radius and center point. This is not an opertaion on the robot, just generating keyframes.. It can feed into a move keyframes node to define a move for a Mecademic arm. Blending is recommended for a smooth circular move.

parameters.name: center_X
parameters.description: The X coordinate of the center of the circle. If not specified, the default value of 0.0 is used.

parameters.name: center_Y
parameters.description: The Y coordinate of the center of the circle. If not specified, the default value of 0.0 is used.

parameters.name: center_Z
parameters.description: The Z coordinate of the center of the circle. If not specified, the default value of 0.0 is used.

parameters.name: radius
parameters.description: The radius of the circle. If not specified, the default value of 0.0 is used.

parameters.name: revolutions
parameters.description: The number of revolutions to make. If not specified, the default value of 1.0 is used.

parameters.name: point_duration
parameters.description: The duration of each point in milliseconds. If not specified, the default value of 500 is used.

returns.description: A dataframe of keyframes to move to.
